What Flyxion is essentially arguing in this monograph is that our foundational assumptions about code...

03:36.580 --> 03:38.340
Like how a program executes, right?

03:38.380 --> 03:38.540
Right.

03:38.620 --> 03:45.580
How it executes, how it manages memory, how it handles time and errors, all of it, they are all built on a syntactic trick.

