And in all these systems, from the 30s to today,

08:35.820 --> 08:41.640
we use these textual markers to define a boundary where certain rules or operations take priority.

08:41.820 --> 08:47.920
But the illusion, Affliction points out, is that we have tricked ourselves into thinking the computation is entirely about the symbols.

08:48.120 --> 08:48.280
Right.

08:48.280 --> 08:53.640
The numbers and the operators, rather than the spaces those symbols inhabit.

08:53.900 --> 08:54.080
Right.

