Yeah.

09:23.300 --> 09:26.940
But the SpherePop calculus asks a critical what-if question.

09:28.000 --> 09:33.340
What if we stop interpreting these parentheses as textual delimiters on a flat page?

09:33.700 --> 09:35.980
What if we stop seeing them as ink on paper,

09:36.180 --> 09:39.620
and instead view them as explicit geometric objects?

09:39.800 --> 09:41.200
And this is where it gets visual.

09:41.460 --> 09:41.740
Right.

09:42.520 --> 09:44.820
Affliction introduces a term for these objects.

09:45.380 --> 09:45.780
Spheres.

09:46.600 --> 09:51.460
In STC, a sphere creates a literal, mathematically bounded region of computation.

09:52.140 --> 09:53.520
It is not just punctuation.

09:53.880 --> 09:55.580
It is a topological space.

09:55.720 --> 09:56.860
A topological space.

09:56.900 --> 09:57.060
Yeah.

09:57.120 --> 10:01.180
It has a definite impermeable inside and a definite separate outside.

10:01.560 --> 10:01.780
Wait.

